[SN]TITLE[SN]
Sunderland sign Anthony Reveillere until end of season

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Sunderland have signed former France international Anthony Reveillere on a deal until the end of the season.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 34-year-old full-back spent last season with Napoli in Italy's Serie A, making 18 appearances before being released at the end of his contract.
Reveillere, who began his career at French club Rennes, was a member of the France squad at both the 2010 World Cup and Euro 2012.
He could make his debut against Arsenal on Saturday.
